name: ExtrinsicSuccess
description: An extrinsic completed successfully.

name: ExtrinsicFailed
description: An extrinsic failed.

name: CodeUpdated
description: `:code` was updated.

name: NewAccount
description: A new account was created.

name: KilledAccount
description: An account was reaped.

name: Remarked
description: On on-chain remark happened.

name: Scheduled
description: Scheduled some task.

name: Canceled
description: Canceled some task.

name: Dispatched
description: Dispatched some task.

name: CallLookupFailed
description: The call for the provided hash was not found so the task has been aborted.

name: Noted
description: A preimage has been noted.

name: Requested
description: A preimage has been requested.

name: Cleared
description: A preimage has ben cleared.

name: IndexAssigned
description: A account index was assigned.

name: IndexFreed
description: A account index has been freed up (unassigned).

name: IndexFrozen
description: A account index has been frozen to its current account ID.

name: Endowed
description: An account was created with some free balance.

name: DustLost
description: An account was removed whose balance was non-zero but below ExistentialDeposit, resulting in an outright loss.

name: Transfer
description: Transfer succeeded.

name: BalanceSet
description: A balance was set by root.

name: Reserved
description: Some balance was reserved (moved from free to reserved).

name: Unreserved
description: Some balance was unreserved (moved from reserved to free).

name: ReserveRepatriated
description: Some balance was moved from the reserve of the first account to the second account. Final argument indicates the destination balance type.

name: Deposit
description: Some amount was deposited (e.g. for transaction fees).

name: Withdraw
description: Some amount was withdrawn from the account (e.g. for transaction fees).

name: Slashed
description: Some amount was removed from the account (e.g. for misbehavior).

name: TransactionFeePaid
description: A transaction fee `actual_fee`, of which `tip` was added to the minimum inclusion fee, has been paid by `who`.

name: EraPaid
description: The era payout has been set; the first balance is the validator-payout; the second is the remainder from the maximum amount of reward.

name: Rewarded
description: The nominator has been rewarded by this amount.

name: Slashed
description: One staker (and potentially its nominators) has been slashed by the given amount.

name: OldSlashingReportDiscarded
description: An old slashing report from a prior era was discarded because it could not be processed.

name: StakersElected
description: A new set of stakers was elected.

name: Bonded
description: An account has bonded this amount. \[stash, amount\]  NOTE: This event is only emitted when funds are bonded via a dispatchable. Notably, it will not be emitted for staking rewards when they are added to stake.

name: Unbonded
description: An account has unbonded this amount.

name: Withdrawn
description: An account has called `withdraw_unbonded` and removed unbonding chunks worth `Balance` from the unlocking queue.

name: Kicked
description: A nominator has been kicked from a validator.

name: StakingElectionFailed
description: The election failed. No new era is planned.

name: Chilled
description: An account has stopped participating as either a validator or nominator.

name: PayoutStarted
description: The stakers' rewards are getting paid.

name: ValidatorPrefsSet
description: A validator has set their preferences.

name: Offence
description: There is an offence reported of the given `kind` happened at the `session_index` and (kind-specific) time slot. This event is not deposited for duplicate slashes. \[kind, timeslot\].

name: NewSession
description: New session has happened. Note that the argument is the session index, not the block number as the type might suggest.

name: NewAuthorities
description: New authority set has been applied.

name: Paused
description: Current authority set has been paused.

name: Resumed
description: Current authority set has been resumed.

name: HeartbeatReceived
description: A new heartbeat was received from `AuthorityId`.

name: AllGood
description: At the end of the session, no offence was committed.

name: SomeOffline
description: At the end of the session, at least one validator was found to be offline.

name: Proposed
description: A motion has been proposed by a public account.

name: Tabled
description: A public proposal has been tabled for referendum vote.

name: ExternalTabled
description: An external proposal has been tabled.

name: Started
description: A referendum has begun.

name: Passed
description: A proposal has been approved by referendum.

name: NotPassed
description: A proposal has been rejected by referendum.

name: Cancelled
description: A referendum has been cancelled.

name: Executed
description: A proposal has been enacted.

name: Delegated
description: An account has delegated their vote to another account.

name: Undelegated
description: An account has cancelled a previous delegation operation.

name: Vetoed
description: An external proposal has been vetoed.

name: PreimageNoted
description: A proposal's preimage was noted, and the deposit taken.

name: PreimageUsed
description: A proposal preimage was removed and used (the deposit was returned).

name: PreimageInvalid
description: A proposal could not be executed because its preimage was invalid.

name: PreimageMissing
description: A proposal could not be executed because its preimage was missing.

name: PreimageReaped
description: A registered preimage was removed and the deposit collected by the reaper.

name: Blacklisted
description: A proposal_hash has been blacklisted permanently.

name: Voted
description: An account has voted in a referendum

name: Seconded
description: An account has secconded a proposal

name: ProposalCanceled
description: A proposal got canceled.

name: Proposed
description: A motion (given hash) has been proposed (by given account) with a threshold (given `MemberCount`).

name: Voted
description: A motion (given hash) has been voted on by given account, leaving a tally (yes votes and no votes given respectively as `MemberCount`).

name: Approved
description: A motion was approved by the required threshold.

name: Disapproved
description: A motion was not approved by the required threshold.

name: Executed
description: A motion was executed; result will be `Ok` if it returned without error.

name: MemberExecuted
description: A single member did some action; result will be `Ok` if it returned without error.

name: Closed
description: A proposal was closed because its threshold was reached or after its duration was up.

name: Proposed
description: A motion (given hash) has been proposed (by given account) with a threshold (given `MemberCount`).

name: Voted
description: A motion (given hash) has been voted on by given account, leaving a tally (yes votes and no votes given respectively as `MemberCount`).

name: Approved
description: A motion was approved by the required threshold.

name: Disapproved
description: A motion was not approved by the required threshold.

name: Executed
description: A motion was executed; result will be `Ok` if it returned without error.

name: MemberExecuted
description: A single member did some action; result will be `Ok` if it returned without error.

name: Closed
description: A proposal was closed because its threshold was reached or after its duration was up.

name: NewTerm
description: A new term with new_members. This indicates that enough candidates existed to run the election, not that enough have has been elected. The inner value must be examined for this purpose. A `NewTerm(\[\])` indicates that some candidates got their bond slashed and none were elected, whilst `EmptyTerm` means that no candidates existed to begin with.

name: EmptyTerm
description: No (or not enough) candidates existed for this round. This is different from `NewTerm(\[\])`. See the description of `NewTerm`.

name: ElectionError
description: Internal error happened while trying to perform election.

name: MemberKicked
description: A member has been removed. This should always be followed by either `NewTerm` or `EmptyTerm`.

name: Renounced
description: Someone has renounced their candidacy.

name: CandidateSlashed
description: A candidate was slashed by amount due to failing to obtain a seat as member or runner-up.  Note that old members and runners-up are also candidates.

name: SeatHolderSlashed
description: A seat holder was slashed by amount by being forcefully removed from the set.

name: MemberAdded
description: The given member was added; see the transaction for who.

name: MemberRemoved
description: The given member was removed; see the transaction for who.

name: MembersSwapped
description: Two members were swapped; see the transaction for who.

name: MembersReset
description: The membership was reset; see the transaction for who the new set is.

name: KeyChanged
description: One of the members' keys changed.

name: Dummy
description: Phantom member, never used.

name: Proposed
description: New proposal.

name: Spending
description: We have ended a spend period and will now allocate funds.

name: Awarded
description: Some funds have been allocated.

name: Rejected
description: A proposal was rejected; funds were slashed.

name: Burnt
description: Some of our funds have been burnt.

name: Rollover
description: Spending has finished; this is the amount that rolls over until next spend.

name: Deposit
description: Some funds have been deposited.

name: SpendApproved
description: A new spend proposal has been approved.

name: Claimed
description: Someone claimed some DOTs.

name: VestingUpdated
description: The amount vested has been updated. This could indicate a change in funds available. The balance given is the amount which is left unvested (and thus locked).

name: VestingCompleted
description: An \[account\] has become fully vested.

name: BatchInterrupted
description: Batch of dispatches did not complete fully. Index of first failing dispatch given, as well as the error.

name: BatchCompleted
description: Batch of dispatches completed fully with no error.

name: BatchCompletedWithErrors
description: Batch of dispatches completed but has errors.

name: ItemCompleted
description: A single item within a Batch of dispatches has completed with no error.

name: ItemFailed
description: A single item within a Batch of dispatches has completed with error.

name: DispatchedAs
description: A call was dispatched.

name: IdentitySet
description: A name was set or reset (which will remove all judgements).

name: IdentityCleared
description: A name was cleared, and the given balance returned.

name: IdentityKilled
description: A name was removed and the given balance slashed.

name: JudgementRequested
description: A judgement was asked from a registrar.

name: JudgementUnrequested
description: A judgement request was retracted.

name: JudgementGiven
description: A judgement was given by a registrar.

name: RegistrarAdded
description: A registrar was added.

name: SubIdentityAdded
description: A sub-identity was added to an identity and the deposit paid.

name: SubIdentityRemoved
description: A sub-identity was removed from an identity and the deposit freed.

name: SubIdentityRevoked
description: A sub-identity was cleared, and the given deposit repatriated from the main identity account to the sub-identity account.

name: ProxyExecuted
description: A proxy was executed correctly, with the given.

name: PureCreated
description: A pure account has been created by new proxy with given disambiguation index and proxy type.

name: Announced
description: An announcement was placed to make a call in the future.

name: ProxyAdded
description: A proxy was added.

name: ProxyRemoved
description: A proxy was removed.

name: NewMultisig
description: A new multisig operation has begun.

name: MultisigApproval
description: A multisig operation has been approved by someone.

name: MultisigExecuted
description: A multisig operation has been executed.

name: MultisigCancelled
description: A multisig operation has been cancelled.

name: BountyProposed
description: New bounty proposal.

name: BountyRejected
description: A bounty proposal was rejected; funds were slashed.

name: BountyBecameActive
description: A bounty proposal is funded and became active.

name: BountyAwarded
description: A bounty is awarded to a beneficiary.

name: BountyClaimed
description: A bounty is claimed by beneficiary.

name: BountyCanceled
description: A bounty is cancelled.

name: BountyExtended
description: A bounty expiry is extended.

name: Added
description: A child-bounty is added.

name: Awarded
description: A child-bounty is awarded to a beneficiary.

name: Claimed
description: A child-bounty is claimed by beneficiary.

name: Canceled
description: A child-bounty is cancelled.

name: NewTip
description: A new tip suggestion has been opened.

name: TipClosing
description: A tip suggestion has reached threshold and is closing.

name: TipClosed
description: A tip suggestion has been closed.

name: TipRetracted
description: A tip suggestion has been retracted.

name: TipSlashed
description: A tip suggestion has been slashed.

name: SolutionStored
description: A solution was stored with the given compute.  If the solution is signed, this means that it hasn't yet been processed. If the solution is unsigned, this means that it has also been processed.  The `bool` is `true` when a previous solution was ejected to make room for this one.

name: ElectionFinalized
description: The election has been finalized, with the given computation and score.

name: ElectionFailed
description: An election failed.  Not much can be said about which computes failed in the process.

name: Rewarded
description: An account has been rewarded for their signed submission being finalized.

name: Slashed
description: An account has been slashed for submitting an invalid signed submission.

name: SignedPhaseStarted
description: The signed phase of the given round has started.

name: UnsignedPhaseStarted
description: The unsigned phase of the given round has started.

name: Rebagged
description: Moved an account from one bag to another.

name: ScoreUpdated
description: Updated the score of some account to the given amount.

name: Created
description: A pool has been created.

name: Bonded
description: A member has became bonded in a pool.

name: PaidOut
description: A payout has been made to a member.

name: Unbonded
description: A member has unbonded from their pool.  - `balance` is the corresponding balance of the number of points that has been   requested to be unbonded (the argument of the `unbond` transaction) from the bonded   pool. - `points` is the number of points that are issued as a result of `balance` being dissolved into the corresponding unbonding pool. - `era` is the era in which the balance will be unbonded. In the absence of slashing, these values will match. In the presence of slashing, the number of points that are issued in the unbonding pool will be less than the amount requested to be unbonded.

name: Withdrawn
description: A member has withdrawn from their pool.  The given number of `points` have been dissolved in return of `balance`.  Similar to `Unbonded` event, in the absence of slashing, the ratio of point to balance will be 1.

name: Destroyed
description: A pool has been destroyed.

name: StateChanged
description: The state of a pool has changed

name: MemberRemoved
description: A member has been removed from a pool.  The removal can be voluntary (withdrawn all unbonded funds) or involuntary (kicked).

name: RolesUpdated
description: The roles of a pool have been updated to the given new roles. Note that the depositor can never change.

name: PoolSlashed
description: The active balance of pool `pool_id` has been slashed to `balance`.

name: UnbondingPoolSlashed
description: The unbond pool at `era` of pool `pool_id` has been slashed to `balance`.

name: Unstaked
description: A staker was unstaked.

name: Slashed
description: A staker was slashed for requesting fast-unstake whilst being exposed.

name: Checking
description: A staker was partially checked for the given eras, but the process did not finish.

name: Errored
description: Some internal error happened while migrating stash. They are removed as head as a consequence.

name: InternalError
description: An internal error happened. Operations will be paused now.

name: CandidateBacked
description: A candidate was backed. `[candidate, head_data]`

name: CandidateIncluded
description: A candidate was included. `[candidate, head_data]`

name: CandidateTimedOut
description: A candidate timed out. `[candidate, head_data]`

name: CurrentCodeUpdated
description: Current code has been updated for a Para. `para_id`

name: CurrentHeadUpdated
description: Current head has been updated for a Para. `para_id`

name: CodeUpgradeScheduled
description: A code upgrade has been scheduled for a Para. `para_id`

name: NewHeadNoted
description: A new head has been noted for a Para. `para_id`

name: ActionQueued
description: A para has been queued to execute pending actions. `para_id`

name: PvfCheckStarted
description: The given para either initiated or subscribed to a PVF check for the given validation code. `code_hash` `para_id`

name: PvfCheckAccepted
description: The given validation code was accepted by the PVF pre-checking vote. `code_hash` `para_id`

name: PvfCheckRejected
description: The given validation code was rejected by the PVF pre-checking vote. `code_hash` `para_id`

name: InvalidFormat
description: Upward message is invalid XCM. \[ id \]

name: UnsupportedVersion
description: Upward message is unsupported version of XCM. \[ id \]

name: ExecutedUpward
description: Upward message executed with the given outcome. \[ id, outcome \]

name: WeightExhausted
description: The weight limit for handling upward messages was reached. \[ id, remaining, required \]

name: UpwardMessagesReceived
description: Some upward messages have been received and will be processed. \[ para, count, size \]

name: OverweightEnqueued
description: The weight budget was exceeded for an individual upward message.  This message can be later dispatched manually using `service_overweight` dispatchable using the assigned `overweight_index`.  \[ para, id, overweight_index, required \]

name: OverweightServiced
description: Upward message from the overweight queue was executed with the given actual weight used.  \[ overweight_index, used \]

name: OpenChannelRequested
description: Open HRMP channel requested. `[sender, recipient, proposed_max_capacity, proposed_max_message_size]`

name: OpenChannelCanceled
description: An HRMP channel request sent by the receiver was canceled by either party. `[by_parachain, channel_id]`

name: OpenChannelAccepted
description: Open HRMP channel accepted. `[sender, recipient]`

name: ChannelClosed
description: HRMP channel closed. `[by_parachain, channel_id]`

name: DisputeInitiated
description: A dispute has been initiated. \[candidate hash, dispute location\]

name: DisputeConcluded
description: A dispute has concluded for or against a candidate. `\[para id, candidate hash, dispute result\]`

name: DisputeTimedOut
description: A dispute has timed out due to insufficient participation. `\[para id, candidate hash\]`

name: Revert
description: A dispute has concluded with supermajority against a candidate. Block authors should no longer build on top of this head and should instead revert the block at the given height. This should be the number of the child of the last known valid block in the chain.

name: NewLeasePeriod
description: A new `[lease_period]` is beginning.

name: Leased
description: A para has won the right to a continuous set of lease periods as a parachain. First balance is any extra amount reserved on top of the para's existing deposit. Second balance is the total amount reserved.

name: AuctionStarted
description: An auction started. Provides its index and the block number where it will begin to close and the first lease period of the quadruplet that is auctioned.

name: AuctionClosed
description: An auction ended. All funds become unreserved.

name: Reserved
description: Funds were reserved for a winning bid. First balance is the extra amount reserved. Second is the total.

name: Unreserved
description: Funds were unreserved since bidder is no longer active. `[bidder, amount]`

name: ReserveConfiscated
description: Someone attempted to lease the same slot twice for a parachain. The amount is held in reserve but no parachain slot has been leased.

name: BidAccepted
description: A new bid has been accepted as the current winner.

name: WinningOffset
description: The winning offset was chosen for an auction. This will map into the `Winning` storage map.

name: Created
description: Create a new crowdloaning campaign.

name: Contributed
description: Contributed to a crowd sale.

name: Withdrew
description: Withdrew full balance of a contributor.

name: PartiallyRefunded
description: The loans in a fund have been partially dissolved, i.e. there are some left over child keys that still need to be killed.

name: AllRefunded
description: All loans in a fund have been refunded.

name: Dissolved
description: Fund is dissolved.

name: HandleBidResult
description: The result of trying to submit a new bid to the Slots pallet.

name: Edited
description: The configuration to a crowdloan has been edited.

name: MemoUpdated
description: A memo has been updated.

name: AddedToNewRaise
description: A parachain has been moved to `NewRaise`

name: Attempted
description: Execution of an XCM message was attempted.  \[ outcome \]

name: Sent
description: A XCM message was sent.  \[ origin, destination, message \]

name: UnexpectedResponse
description: Query response received which does not match a registered query. This may be because a matching query was never registered, it may be because it is a duplicate response, or because the query timed out.  \[ origin location, id \]

name: ResponseReady
description: Query response has been received and is ready for taking with `take_response`. There is no registered notification call.  \[ id, response \]

name: Notified
description: Query response has been received and query is removed. The registered notification has been dispatched and executed successfully.  \[ id, pallet index, call index \]

name: NotifyOverweight
description: Query response has been received and query is removed. The registered notification could not be dispatched because the dispatch weight is greater than the maximum weight originally budgeted by this runtime for the query result.  \[ id, pallet index, call index, actual weight, max budgeted weight \]

name: NotifyDispatchError
description: Query response has been received and query is removed. There was a general error with dispatching the notification call.  \[ id, pallet index, call index \]

name: NotifyDecodeFailed
description: Query response has been received and query is removed. The dispatch was unable to be decoded into a `Call`; this might be due to dispatch function having a signature which is not `(origin, QueryId, Response)`.  \[ id, pallet index, call index \]

name: InvalidResponder
description: Expected query response has been received but the origin location of the response does not match that expected. The query remains registered for a later, valid, response to be received and acted upon.  \[ origin location, id, expected location \]

name: InvalidResponderVersion
description: Expected query response has been received but the expected origin location placed in storage by this runtime previously cannot be decoded. The query remains registered.  This is unexpected (since a location placed in storage in a previously executing runtime should be readable prior to query timeout) and dangerous since the possibly valid response will be dropped. Manual governance intervention is probably going to be needed.  \[ origin location, id \]

name: ResponseTaken
description: Received query response has been read and removed.  \[ id \]

name: AssetsTrapped
description: Some assets have been placed in an asset trap.  \[ hash, origin, assets \]

name: VersionChangeNotified
description: An XCM version change notification message has been attempted to be sent.  \[ destination, result \]

name: SupportedVersionChanged
description: The supported version of a location has been changed. This might be through an automatic notification or a manual intervention.  \[ location, XCM version \]

name: NotifyTargetSendFail
description: A given location which had a version change subscription was dropped owing to an error sending the notification to it.  \[ location, query ID, error \]

name: NotifyTargetMigrationFail
description: A given location which had a version change subscription was dropped owing to an error migrating the location to our new XCM format.  \[ location, query ID \]
